inn1.comm: Anderson hits a good length just outside off stump immediately, and gets the ball to move away from Watson, who lets it go.
another one moves away from a good length closer to off stump, Watson pokes at it this time and is beaten. This pitch doesn't seem to be that quick though
after two balls jag away, this one holds its line and rears up at Watson from short of a length, he takes one hand off the bat as he fends towards point
defended on the front foot towards the off side
top start from Anderson, four accurate deliveries, Watson gets behind the line of this one and defends on the off side
a touch wider outside off stump, Watson doesn't have to play at it and so he lets it go. Anderson returns to the side with a maiden
Warner stays in his crease and lets the ball go as it seams across him
a fuller ball outside off stump, Warner stays back and lets the ball pass again
a full ball just outside off stump, Warner pushes towards mid-off
short of a length outside off stump, Warner shoulders arms
Australia stay scoreless as Warner stays back and defends on the off side
the ball lifts off a good length outside off stump, Warner watches it pass just outside off stump
runs at last, via an outside edge past the empty gully region as Watson moves forward and tries to punch a good length ball that seams away from him
Warner braces for the movement into him from Anderson and pushes towards extra cover
wider outside the off stump this time, Warner lets it go to Kieswetter
Warner lifts his bat out of the way of a short of a length ball that pitches around off and slants away from the left-hander
good length outside off stump, Warner lets it the ball again. England's bowlers have given Australia nothing so far to hit
Anderson gets the ball to jag away sharply after pitching on a good length around off stump, Warner shoulders arms
runs, again via an outside edge through the empty gully region. This time the ball was edged in the air. Watson came forward to drive a good length ball, which moved away from him
short of a length at Warner's body, he gets behind the line and defends
Warner stays back and defends a straight ball on a good length towards the leg side
Finn hits a good length outside off and the ball jags towards Kieswetter's right after Warner lets it go
Warner stays on the back foot and defends towards the off side
Warner finally gets off the mark by getting awkwardly on top of the bounce of a short of a length delivery and swatting the ball down through cover. Not timed well.
a swish and a miss outside off stump, Warner stayed back and reached for the ball as it seamed away from him
another swish outside off stump and this time the ball hits the edge and flies down to third man
defended on the off side towards cover, where Bopara fields.
Anderson swings the ball into the right-hander this time, Watson comes forward and blocks
Watson strides forward and drives a full ball gently between cover and point. The first proper scoring shot of the day
Anderson gets a bit straighter and Watson plays the ball towards midwicket

a huge appeal for lbw but the umpire is unmoved. England have asked for a review. The ball was full and straight. Warner should have been playing forward but he wasn't. He hasn't played forward to anything today. He tried to close the face of the bat this time and play towards square, he missed and was struck plumb in front. That ball pitched on leg and middle and was going to hit middle. Plumb.

and he's now the old batsman. That looks plumb. Finn is keeping the ball very full, and this time he moves it back into the right-hander. Forrest prodded from his crease and was smacked flush on the back pad. He has a quick word with Watson, presumably about a review, and then marches right off. That ball was smashing into off and middle.

oh my word, what a hat-trick ball! Finn pitches on a good length outside off and seams the ball sharply into Clarke, who strode forward to defend. The ball cut through the gap between bat and body and passed over the top of the stumps. Phew.
Clarke's staying in his crease now, and digs out a full ball with the bottom of his bat
full and straight, Clarke stays in his crease and plays back to the bowler
good length and straight, Clarke gets behind the line and defends back down the pitch, a double-wicket maiden.
good length, pitching on off and angling into Watson, who gets behind the line on the back foot and defends
Watson gets hit on the thigh pad by one that is a bit to straight and moves into the right-hander
hits a good length outside off and holds its line, a nice follow-up ball after two that came into the right-hander, Watson let it go through to the keeper
the ball jags back into Watson and hits him on the front pad, he had got outside the line of off stump while trying to defend though
a full ball swinging into off and middle stump, Watson defends on the front foot towards cover
a little too straight again, Watson moves forward and across and glances the ball towards fine leg
good length outside off stump, Clarke shoulders arms
a half-volley around off stump, and Clarke meets it with the full face of the bat and drives towards Finn, who gets some hand on it and deflects the ball towards mid-off
that is the first poor ball of the morning, a full toss outside off stump, Clarke drives it through cover for the innings' first boundary
that is a gem from Finn, he hit a good length just outside off stump and got the ball to straighten on the right-hander, Clarke lunged forward to defend but was beaten
full and straight, Clarke tries to flick but gets a thick inside edge past Bell at short leg
a good leave, left it on bounce after the ball pitched on a good length, it passed over off stump
Anderson pitches outside off and jags the ball into the right-hander, Watson defends
a huge appeal from Anderson once again but I think Watson got his front pad outside the line of off stump, might have got an inside edge on it as well
Watson pushes forward to defend again and plays it towards the off side
defended on the back foot towards the bowler
another loud appeal for lbw as Watson defends on the front foot, the ball hit him just outside the line and was a bit high as well
defended on the front foot
short of a length outside off stump and the ball holds its line to beat Clarke's defensive push
fuller length around off stump, Clarke stays in his crease and drives towards mid-off
a half-volley around off stump and Clarke drives wide of the fielder at mid-off for a single
a full ball swings into the middle of the bat as Watson moves forward to drive, but he hits it to the man at mid-off
short of a length on middle and off, Watson gets behind the line and defends
good length on off and middle, Watson defends from his crease towards the off side. This is probably the hardest start to an ODI match in ages
Clarke pushes a full ball coming into him towards cover and the batsmen run a single after a moment's hesitation
Watson strides forward to defend but he was playing for the movement into him, the ball held its line outside off and beat the bat
a loud appeal for lbw but the umpire says not out. England will not review it this time. Bresnan jagged the ball back into the right hander and hit the pad. It was too high
played off the back foot towards the of side
a little too straight from Bresnan and Watson whips the ball off his pads behind square

dropped at point! Clarke drove at a full ball outside off and edged it towards Morgan, it went straight to him and fell straight out as well. That's a sitter. Don't think he got much hand on it actually, seemed to thud into his chest.
good length but a bit too wide outside off for Clarke to want to play a shot
full on off stump, Clarke moves forward and drives to the man at mid-off
good length and the ball straightens outside off stump to beat Clarke's defences
fuller ball outside off, Clarke leans forward and drives through wide mid-off, the fielder gives chase
good length just outside off stump, Watson moves forward and defends
defended on the front foot towards point
good length outside off stump, the batsman lets it go
Clarke leans forward and plays an elegant cover drive to a full ball, but it's to the fielder
good length on off stump, defended back to the bowler
on middle and leg stump, Clarke stays back and flicks the ball through square leg
full ball on middle stump, Clarke leans across and drives the ball through midwicket
good length outside off stump, Clarke strides out and shoulders arms
Broad keeps it full and beats Watson, who came forward to defend. He was playing for the angle into him but the delivery held its line outside off stump
that's the first shot Watson's played with authority today. He came forward to a half-volley and thumped the ball hard between the bowler and mid-off
defended on the front foot
short of a length ball outside off stump, Watson is beaten on the cut
Australia have a free hit. Broad over-stepped as he delivered a full ball on off stump, which Watson played back to him
he's smashed it, off the front foot. The length was not full, Watson came forward and pulled across the line, lofting the ball over the long-on boundary, it just cleared the rope
driven off the front foot through cover, that will make it 14 off the over, the best over for Australia by a mile
good length outside off stump, played off the back foot towards cover
Watson heaves across the line at one that isn't short enough to pull from outside off stump, the ball passes under his bat
good length delivery angling into the right-hander, Watson moves forward and pushes towards mid-on
full ball outside off stump, Clarke moves forward and plays towards cover
Clarke moved forward and across to on-drive but got a bit of inside edge on to the pad
good length outside off stump, Clarke moves forward and defends towards cover
good length on off stump, Watson stays back and opens the face to steer the ball towards point
shot! Too full from Broad and Watson strides forward and meets it with a wonderfully straight bat, driving with power past the bowler. Broad tried to get down quickly but had no chance
a bit of room outside off and Watson cuts past gully towards third man
pitches on a good length outside off stump and seams slightly away from Clarke,who stays back and shoulders arms.
Broad pitches on a good length and seams it away from Watson, who stays back and prods inside the line of the ball
Clarke strides out to defend but gets an outside edge that runs towards third man
Watson is struck on the front pad as he moves forward to defend, Bresnan appeals but the impact was outside the line of off stump
good length around off stump, Watson comes forward and defends on the off side
short of a length outside off stump, Watson has width and so he cuts hard, Morgan dives to his right and saves three runs at point
too full and Clarke comes forward to drive, he begins to run but the ball eventually beats the fielder diving across from mid-off
good length outside off stump, Clarke strides forward and shoulders arms
that's gone over middle stump! Bresnan pitched around off and jagged the ball back into Clarke, who came forward to defend but was cut in half
the first ball is a bit straight but Watson fails to connect while trying to whip off his pads
short of a length outside off, Watson stays back and cuts the ball past the fielder at gully
that's a half-volley on the pads, Clarke leans forward and across and flicks to the square-leg boundary to bring up the 50 partnership with Watson
full and straight, on off and middle, Clarke plays the ball towards Anderson
good length on off and middle, Clarke defends from his crease
Anderson appeals for lbw but he's largely on his own this time. The ball nipped back from a good length and struck Clarke high on the back pad before going towards the gully region
defended on the back foot towards the off side
good length around off stump, Watson moves forward to defend
bowled him! Watson tried to steer towards third man but the ball was too full and jagged back sharply into the right-hander. He was cramped for room and ended up bottom edging on to middle stump
good length on off stump,Bailey stays in his crease and pushes on the leg side
Clarke stays on the back foot and plays towards midwicket
steered off the front foot through point for a single
good length outside off stump, the ball holds its line, Clarke lets it pass
Anderson swings one into the blockhole, Clarke moves forward and plays to midwicket
good length on of stump, Clarke gets behind the line and defends
good length on off and middle, Clarke moves forward and drives to midwicket
Anderson pitches on off stump and gets the ball to straighten on Clarke, who closes the bat face ever so slightly and gets an outside edge towards point
good length outside off, Clarke punches from the crease towards cover
short and wide outside off stump, Bailey cuts hard off the back foot and through the gap at point
defended from the crease towards the off side
played off the pads in front of square for a single
Clarke cuts the ball in front of point for a quick single
Bailey's been cut in half as he tried to defend one that jagged back into him from the crease. He was beaten between bat and body
Bailey was trying to drive towards extra cover but got an inside edge past square leg instead
full ball outside off stump, Bailey drives to mid off
a low full toss, which Bailey drives to the fielder at mid-on
full ball outside off stump, Bailey moves forward and plays the square drive, placing the ball towards Morgan's left at point

that is a terrific ball and it's bowled Bailey! Bopara pitched the ball on a good length around middle stump and got it to straighten and leave the right-hander just enough to beat the outside edge of Bailey's forward push and clip the top of off stump. McGrath would have approved of that one
good length outside off, Hussey lets it pass

Bopara roars the appeal for lbw after the yorker strikes Hussey on the boot. Umpire Nigel Llong says not out and Cook has asked for the review. The ball swung a long way into the right-hander, Hussey was playing forward from his crease and missed as he aimed for midwicket. Replays show the ball clipping leg stump but that's not good enough to overturn the on-field umpire's decision. Hussey survives, and is a trifle lucky to.
good length on off stump, played past the bowler towards mid-on, a loud shout of "Wait" from Clarke and they don't run in the end

has that hit Clarke's inside edge? England have no reviews left. No inside edge. The ball jagged from a good length into the right-hander and beat Clarke's forward push. That hit him in line with middle stump and would have knocked over leg stump. England can't review it though, after the unsuccessful review against Hussey in Bopara's over.
flicked through square leg for a single
driven on the front foot towards mid off
flicked off the pads behind square
good length on off stump, played from the crease towards point
defended on the off side
pushed towards point off the front foot
full ball on off stump, driven on the front foot to mid-off
good length outside off stump, Clarke prods away from his body and is beaten
good length again, this time angling into the right-hander, Clarke defends on the leg side
clipped off the pads through midwicket
fuller length on off stump, punched off the front foot through cover
hits a good length around off and nips into the right-hander, Hussey stays back and blocks
Hussey stays back again and knocks the ball into the gap at cover
good length outside off, Clarke lifts his bat out of the way
good length a little wider outside off stump, the batsman lets it pass

edged and has that carried? If it has, it's been dropped, but atough chance. Clarke came forward to drive and got an outside edge that went right between the keeper and first slip. Kieswetter dived to hisright, Anderson dived to his left but the ball went down.
left outside off
better ball that beats the outside edge
another one on a great length and has Clarke feeling outside off and getting beaten again
touch shorter and pulled out to deep midwicket
defended from a full length just outside off
played to cover again, this time with a firmer push but the fielder comes in to take a single
forward and pressed to point
unsure of coming forward, blocked into the covers
angled in from back of a length, off the pad into the off side
forward with bat and pad together, pushed to cover
forward to block more concertedly into the covers
fuller and pushed through cover, the fielder goes back and prevents the second run
length which beats the attempted turn to leg, off the pad into the off side
full and pushed towards mid on and, oh dear Broad is beaten on the slide and it trickles away for four
wowzer is this close to the off stump, left alone and it nips back and just goes over the off stump
pushed wide of extra cover for a sharp single
full and wide, Clarke enticed to play a drive and it ends up being a wild swipe that misses
Clarke beaten again! Fabulous stuff from Bopara
shouldered arms outside off
full and left alone outside off
another huge shout for an lbw by Broad, again turned down because of height one assumes and indeed it is so this time it's a good decision
blocked on the crease around off stump
length around middle and off, pushed to mid on, they consider and then refuse the single
full just outside off stump and pushed to cover
full and dug out to point
good length, played slightly around the pad down to long leg
blocked on off stump back up the wicket
turned to midwicket on a length
driven outside off, comes off an inside edge towards square leg, it was a loose drive to the wrong length but they get one
back foot punch out past point
ran down to third man
tucked into midwicket from a good length around middle and off
good length and defended back up the wicket
played into the off side on the back foot
cracking delivery drawing Clarke forward and driving, the ball seamed away and bounced beating Clarke all ends up
bumper and ducked
played with nice soft hands down to third man
full and punched down to long on
outside off and guided to point on the crease
cut out to deep cover
played forward and guided into the covers
little bit of width, Clarke coming forward and guided down to third man
excellent restart, this jags back off the seam and Clarke sort of back foot drive aimed at cover gets an inside edge to fine leg for four, lucky Clarke again

cleaned him up now though and this is a cracker, a length ball seams back and takes the off and middle stumps. It's another great length, wasn't right up there to drive and Clarke got in a bad position, missed by a long way and his off stump ended up on the floor

gone first ball again! And what a catch! Craig Kieswetter has flung himself to his right and taken a blinder on the juggle. It is a super delivery, back of length that zipped through and took an inside edge, Kieswetter took off, parried with the first attempted and then grabbed it as he fell to the ground
length outside off and left, not the best hat-trick ball, needed to make him play
bouncer that Lee sways away from and it comes off his arm to the keeper
width outside off and full, cracked away through the off side, belting stroke
stinker down leg side, miles wide
responds with a ball outside off that wobbles in, well left
full and punched to cover from just outside off stump
this time he gets the drive past extra cover, just opening the face to steer it past the fielder, good stroke
driven again, this time back to the bowler, did it carry to Bopara? Yep it did, out of the fingertips
guided down to third man with an open face
back foot and punched to point
full and pushed to point who dives and half-saves, they take a single
length ball that nips back and takes an inside edge as Lee tried to awkwardly fend it off, goes to fine leg
back of a length and a cut and miss
tried to same stroke to a fuller length, played and missed again
a sand-wedge over the bowler, taken off a length over the bowler's head it plugs absolutely dead in the outfield
more length this time and kept out back to bowler
driven from outside off, comes off an inside edge to leg
chipped in front of square leg
a little too straight again and worked through square leg
better line and just dropped into the leg side
blocked again back up the wicket
back of a length and blocked awkwardly, Lee was unsure where that ended up
full and driven, a hand at extra cover saves four but they still get a run
just back of length and blocked on the crease
turned from a fuller length through square leg
back of a length and dropped square on the leg side again
width offered and again Lee throws the hands at it, slapping to mid off
full and pushed to cover
width and cut for four, a gift and Hussey cashed in
back to block around the off stump
good length, Hussey stays in his crease and turns towards midwicket
length on off stump and blocked to cover
leg side wide
length and blocked on middle and off
similarly defended
guided toward point on the off side
bumper and ducked beneath
back of a length and played back up the wicket on the back foot
tucked awkwardly through the leg side
back of a length into the thigh pad and Hussey tried to turn it around the corner
turned to midwicket and another midfield gives away a single
short and wide, would have been an extra had Hussey not attempted to cut, he only got it to cover too
dropped towards cover
Lee gave himself a little bit of room there but left a short ball outside off
fired in full at the pads, ricochets to cover
bumper and ducked but too short and called wide
another short ball, Lee steps away to try and cut again but misses
length and turned to the 45
forward and blocked back up the wicket
that is awesome, turn and bounce past the outside edge, what a delivery
down the wicket, Lee not to the pitch and blocked with the pad
more turn and it's off the outside edge high on the bat to backward point who was just moved there
this is too short though and punched down wide of long off for a two, well ran
blocked just outside off
short and cut out wide of deep cover so they can get back for the second
full toss and missed out, only finding the bowler
pushed back up the pitch from just outside off
hit into the deep, Bell screams in from deep cover to get there, gets two hands to it but can't hold on and another chance is missed by England
blocked around off stump
pushed down to long off from a full length
flighted up and pushed down to long off
middle and leg, ran back to the bowler
down the wicket and blocked with bat and pad
floated up, dropped carefully to the leg side and the scamper through for a run
driven firmly to extra cover
driven softer to the same fielder
off stump on a length, pushed in to cover
slapped towards long off but it goes hardly anywhere meaning they can get two, landing between extra cover going back and long off coming in
pushed on the ground this time to long on
driven and a edge past the wicketkeeper diving at full stretch to third man for four
full and flicked to midwicket
shorted outside off and left alone
back and worked down to long on, they come back and Lee with a dive takes the second
floated up and it's leg side, steered very fine for four
and now short and pulled wide of long on, finds the gap well
pushed for a single to extra cover
another single through the off side
back of a length and cut out through point for two wide of deep cover
shot! Picked up from a full length on leg stump and he whacks it with great timing over deep square leg

but this time finds the fielder, holing out to long on, was the necessary? It was mistimed and Broad came in to take a comfortable catch. Having just taken a six was another big heave required? Five singles, 11 off the over would do. After a lovely little innings that was a poor way to go really
length and dropped into the off side for a single
back of a length outside off and guided to point
pushed square on the off side
cut at and missed outside off
forward and blocked into the covers
pushing at a length ball just outside off, another great length
full and there's a noise as McKay drives, the noise was bat on pad, good decision
leg side
drive and a miss again, this time he definitely hit his pad
forward to block just outside off, solid that time
dropped into the leg side so McKay will keep the strike, England will like that
short and pulled for four, may England won't like McKay on strike, wonderful stroke, perfect technique
blocked around middle and off, they consider flashing through for a run but decide not too

smashed up in the air, so high up, miles up and well taken by Bresnan at mid off, fine take diving backwards in the the end, McKay tried to go down the ground with a drive but simply went high and nowhere near long enough
full and smashed down to long off
played forward and eased through cover
opened his body and guided to third man
step away and cut past point, Trott comes around and saves four, they take a couple
heaved down to long on this time there's no chance of a second run
back of a length ball that rears up slightly but it's guided down well for a run behind square on the off side
great shot, straight down the ground over the bowler's head and it's well timed too
slower outside off, cut to point and they scramble through for the run
swing and a miss outside off
meets it on the full and gets it behind square on the leg side for four, helped around the corner
nearly the same again, in fact this beats midwicket and runs for four more, another shot helped into the leg side having met it on the full
caught on the boundary and Hussey falls trying to find the rope again, slugging a length ball towards long off, Anderson comes round and claims the comfortable chance
slapped over midwicket, not quite timed but two more
belted down the ground and the charge back for two to long off who retuned poorly
dug out towards long on and they get two again

inn2.comm: good length angling across the left-hander, Cook moves forward and defends
fuller length but wider outside off stump, Cook lets it go
the ball rears off a good length and slants across Cook, who has a poke off the back foot and is beaten
Cook moves forward and defends a good length ball on the leg side
good length pitching outside off stump, Cook moves forward, covers his off stump, and shoulders arms
Cook goes back to a good length ball and plays on the off side
pitches on a good length on off and bends it slightly away from Bell, who stays in his crease, covers for the movement and defends on the off side
this time the line is down leg side, Bell can't connect with the glance
pitches on off stump and seams away from the right-hander, Bell moves forward to defend and is beaten
defended on the leg side
wider outside off stump this time, Bell lets it go
good length outside off once again, Bell lets it go through to Wade
Bell moves forward and across to defend a good length ball towards mid-on
full length angling into the left-hander from round the wicket, Cook moves forward and plays towards mid-off
short and wide outside off stump, Cook helps himself to an easy boundary by cutting the ball through point
Lee angles the ball into the left-hander, a fuller length, Cook moves his front foot out side the line of off stump and defends on the leg side
fuller length but wider outside off stump, Cook frees his arms again and slashes the ball through point. That's two loose balls already from Australia. England gave away nothing
short of a length outside off stump, Cook is enjoying the angle from around the wicket, the ball comes in at him, he punches off the back foot through cover
Bell stays back and plays a full ball awkwardly towards cover, he should have been more forward to that delivery
good length and straight, defended on the off side
Hilfenhaus tries to bend it away from a middle stump line, but it doesn't happen, Bell taps between midwicket and mid-on
Cook moves forward and opens the face to steer towards third man
Bell stays in his crease and steers a short of a length ball towards third man
good length on off stump, Cook stays on his crease and defends
full and straight, Cook plays towards mid-off
good length on off stump, defended on the off side
good length around off stump, Bell steps out and defends
glorious, flowing drive from Bell, who came forward to a length ball and drove on the up while on the move. He placed it wide of mid-off and all the way to the boundary
he comes out again and drives through midwicket

huge appeal for lbw but the umpire says not out. McKay nipped the ball off a good length back into the right-hander and hit the pad. Bell was forward and the ball hit high. Probably would have gone over the stumps.
this time McKay gets the ball to hold its line around off stump and beats Bell, who tries to defend
Cook stays in his crease and square drives through point
good length and straight, defended on the off side
Bell comes out of his crease again, and taps the ball towards midwicket
good length and straight, Bell moves out of his crease and defends
Bell comes out again but this time he gets beaten outside off stump
full ball and this time Bell clips it off his pads through midwicket, the fielder chases successfully
Bell gets hit on the thigh by one that nips into him from a good length, he had stepped out of his ground
a fuller ball angling into the right-hander, Bell stays in his crease this time and taps the ball towards midwicket
good length outside off, Bell covers his stumps and shoulders arms
good length coming into off stump, Bell goes out to meet it and defends on the leg side
good length outside off, Bell lets it go through to the keeper
played from the crease towards point
too full on the pads, a poor start from Pattinson, Bell clips the ball off his pads behind square. Pattinson had overstepped as well, so Bell has a free-hit coming up
Bell charged too early and swung too early at a slower ball, a slower full toss. He mis-hit it towards the bowler
played from the crease off the pads towards midwicket
Bell stays back and defends a good length ball towards point
good length on off stump, Bell meets the delivery on the front foot and blocks
good length angling into off stump, Bell gets behind the line and blocks
sublime shot, Bell moves forward and across and flicks the ball off his pads between midwicket and mid-on, superbly timed as well
and he gets beaten by one that seams across him from a good length
pitches wider outside off stump and slants away from Cook, who plays no shot
good length and straight, defended back to the bowler
McKay hits the pad as Cook pushes forward but that's slanting across and missing off stump, umpire Erasmus turns down the appeal for lbw. There was an inside edge as well
flicked off the pads towards midwicket
good length and straight yet again, Cook stays in his crease and blocks
Bell defends from his crease but gets beaten by one that pitches on a good length and holds its line, Bell ended up playing inside the delivery
this time the ball angles into Bell, who comes forward and defends

edged and just out of reach of the leaping Hussey at second slip, that burnt his fingertips, I think. Bell had reached out for a short of a length ball outside off and tried to crack it through point. He got a thick edge that flew high towards Hussey's right
clipped off the pads towards fine leg
nearly in the blockhole, Bell digs it out on the leg side
good length and straight, Bell stays in his crease and defends toward the bowler
a speedy delivery that pitches on middle and slants across the left-hander, Cook pushes forward and is beaten
dropped, Cook drove the length ball firmly back at McKay, the height was good, McKay went for it with both hands towards his right and the ball hit him on the wrist
played on the off side
good length and straight, defended back to the bowler
Cook tries to play an expansive drive to a good length ball that slants across him, he makes no contact
Cook tries to drive through cover again, the ball is fuller and it flies through the vacant gully region off the outside edge
good length on a wicket to wicket line, Cook stays in his crease, moves slightly across and plays on the leg side
Cook is beaten as he pushes at a ball that slides across him, Wade collects and breaks the stumps but Cook was safe
too full, too wide, Cook reaches for it and cracks the ball through point with a crisp square drive
Cook drives again but this time he edges the fuller ball between first slip and gully
good length outside off stump, Bell plays the ball to gully
good length on middle and off, Bell stays in his crease, because Wade is standing up to the stumps, and defends
good length delivery that rises as it slants across Cook, who lets it pass

a massive appeal as Pattinson hits the pad but umpire Erasmus says not out. Clarke asks for a review quickly. He's bowling from over the wicket to the left-hander, the ball pitched outside leg stump so that's the end of that review. Australia have none left
Cook stays in his crease and defends
driven of the front foot towards mid off
Cook stays back and punches a short of a length ball towards point
Cook chases a wide ball outside off stump, trying to drive through cover, but is beaten
good length outside off stump, Bell stands his ground and chops towards gully
